T SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I don't mean out of bounds saves, there are rules for those. I mean a scenario like this:<br>
<br>
Power armor 3+ save, roll to hit, roll to wound, then under the rules he saves on a 3+. Even with there being special rules for close combat, power weapons, 'nids, and probably heavy weapons doesn't this practically negate small arms fire in favor of no-save weapons? Yes, numbers are a factor but it's still making them a bit hardier than they should be...<br>
<br>
Would seem that it would be better to do hit, then armor save, then wound under this system. I still don't agree with removing save modifiers and keeping armor as it always has been. The modifiers for certain weapons were what kept things balanced. Most weapons you'd want to equip your troops with carried at least a -1.<br>
<br>
As for invincible characters, it still seems that you can have a psyker with a psyche save/d-field/TDarmor. Terminator armor wasn't that big a thing to deal with, they're basically mini-tanks and a heavy weapon had a good chance of killing them. Nids could rip them a new one, and the psyker too once you get close enough.<br>
<br>
Sarissa Candyangel<br>
