<br>
I had a partially painted Eldar army (Saim-Hann!!! WOOHOO!!!) A completely unpainted Dark Angel army, and a painted Space Wolf army. I think, but I'm not sure, (Been a while since I broke out the dice) I had close to 6000 points of each. I also started smaller contingents of Orcs, Imperial Agents, and Dark Eldar. My Eldar force retired from the game undefeated in 3 or 4 years of play. Had a squeaker against a Tyranid force that came down to one victory point, but I pulled it out. In my entire career I lost only one Farseer (mostly due to some ungodly luck)<br>
<br>
Anyone here play Necromunda? I got into that game like a viking. I had Van Saar, Spyrer, and... who were the religious fanatics again? Damn I can't remember. <br>
<br>
I've been putting money into GW games since 1986. I had a first print copy of &quot;Warhammer 40K: Rogue Trader.&quot; That game bore very little resemblance to what came about in 2nd and 3rd edition. I also played Epic (in the Adeptus Titanicus era, before they pooched that system too) and Warhammer Quest. I shudder to think how much I threw down the drain on those games.</font><P>Senelyen Steelheart,<BR>
